<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9197> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9197" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 727, footnote 28" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8861> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8861" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 726, footnote 21" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1593> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1593" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "M. Aemilius Lepidus succeeded M. Aemilius Numida." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1592> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1592" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Bardt (4, 29) has seen that this M. Aemilius Lepidus can hardly be identified with the famous Pont. Max. who was Cos. I in 187 and died about 152. He may be the Praetor of 218 and/or 213." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1590> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1590" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 26.23.7." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1478> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1478" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Took measures against the spread of foreign cults (Liv. 25.1.6-12, cf. 12.3). Reported the frauds of Postumius Pyrgensis to the Senate (25.3.12). See below, note 2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1477> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1477" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Klebs (RE) identifies this Praetor with M. Aemilius, Pr. 218, and the unsuccessful candidate for the consulship of 216 (see 218, note 2). During this period two or three Praetors repeated the office before the prescribed interval of ten years (Liv. 7.2.2; Mommsen, Str. 1.518, note 3, 519, notes 3 and 4): Q. Fulvius Flaccus, 215 and 214, T. Otacilius, 217 and 214, and probably M. Pomponius Matho (217, 216; see 217, note 4), so the exemption granted to ex-Consuls after the battle of Lake Trasimene probably extended to other magistrates. Livy notes each of the iterations mentioned above, but gives no indication that this M. Aemilius had previously held the praetorship. The identification with the Praetor of 218 therefore remains uncertain. M. Aemilius Papus, who died as Curio Maximus in 210, is also a possibility." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1476> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1476" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 24.43.6 Provinces and armies 24.44.2-3, cf. 25.3.4 and 6" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1367> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1367" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Consulted the Senate regarding the request of the Petelini for aid (Liv. 23.20.6) and the supplementing of the membership of the Senate itself (23.22.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1366> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1366" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Aemilius was not one of the Praetors regularly elected for 216 (Liv. 22.35.5-6). Either Livy is mistaken (Hesselbarth, 467, note 1; De Sanctis 3.2.359f.) or there was a Praetor Suffectus (Weissenborn on Livy 23.30.6; D.- G. 5.4, note 8). This is perfectly possible, since the Praetor Urbanus, whose functions we find Aemilius performing, was seriously wounded, and another Praetor was killed late this year in Gaul. De Sanctis urges that the episodes with which Aemilius is connected were inventions of Coelius. Both however are consistent with the conditions of the time." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1297> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1297" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 21.49.6-8, and 51.7; cf. 22.35.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1296> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1296" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The cognomina of Aemilius, Atilius, and Manlius, respectively, are given in the list of unsuccessful candidated for the consulship of 216 (Liv. 22.35.1). An interval of one year between praetorship and consulship was the normal practice at this period (Mommsen, Str. 1.525, note 1)." .
